findings.lower_chest: Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. There is no evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion.

abdominal_findings.liver: Demonstrates homogenous attenuation throughout. No evidence of focal lesions.
abdominal_findings.pancreas: Has normal attenuation throughout, without evidence of focal lesions or pancreatic ductal dilatation.
abdominal_findings.spleen: Shows normal size and attenuation throughout, without evidence of focal lesions.
abdominal_findings.adrenals: Right and left adrenal glands are normal in size and shape.
abdominal_findings.kidneys: Normal and symmetric size with normal nephrogram. No evidence of focal renal lesions or hydronephrosis.
abdominal_findings.gastrointestinal: Stomach unremarkable. Small bowel loops normal caliber, wall thickness, and enhancement. Colon and rectum within normal limits. Appendix dilated to 10 mm, fluid-filled with fecaliths, hyperemia of the wall, mild surrounding inflammatory stranding, no extraluminal air or drainable collection.
abdominal_findings.pelvis: Urinary bladder and distal ureters unremarkable. Trace free fluid in the pelvis.
abdominal_findings.reproductive_organs: Uterus notable for several exophytic fibroids, largest measuring 2.5 x 2.3 x 2.9 cm.
abdominal_findings.lymph_nodes: No retroperitoneal or mesenteric lymphadenopathy. No pelvic or inguinal lymphadenopathy.
abdominal_findings.bones: No evidence of worrisome osseous lesions or acute fracture.
abdominal_findings.soft_tissues: Abdominal and pelvic wall within normal limits.

findings.notification: Patient had been transferred for treatment at time of interpretation.
